name: About Face - Peach Fuzz Chrome Mylar Type II
description:
About Face examines femininity, beauty, and objectification by focusing on a woman's hand holding chrome Mylar mirrors, which reflect the viewer, set against a soft, shimmery peachy-pink marbled background. Isolated facial features appear occasionally, reminding the observer of how we focus on certain aspects of ourselves rather than the whole being. 
The design elements appear to float as we digitally print white ink behind the hands to keep them in the foreground, while the metallic nature of the rest of the print recedes to the background. The mirrors and marbled background add movement to the design and reflect the space and viewers, making the design very dynamic.
Drawing inspiration from the historical role of women as muses and the symbolism of Venus, the artist critiques the idealized representations of women in art and culture.
Shyama Golden, a Texas-born Sri Lankan American artist, brilliantly combines her skills in digital painting and graphic design to scrutinize the intricate layers of identity.

name: Enfumé - Acid Free Eco Fibrous
description:
Enfumé is a nouveau interpretation of a French scenic wallpaper that offers a calming, mountainous escape. Painterly details of brush strokes add texture and showcase that muralists hand-painted the original artwork for this digitally printed wallpaper designed by Jon Sherman. The lifelike scale and variety of flora result in a peaceful room setting that feels like a stroll through a lush park.
The Acid Free colorway has a subdued palette with a light blue sky and mountains, pink and white cherry blossom trees, green Spanish moss covered oak trees, fan palms, elephant ear plants, and ground cover, with white irises scattered about.
Flavor Paper founder and creative director Jon Sherman is a self-trained artist and designer whose work has been featured in numerous museums, books, and projects.

name: Ali - Air Silver Mylar
description:
Ali is based on two Andy Warhol Polaroids of Muhammad Ali taken in 1977 as part of his Athletes series. Warhol managed to capture a powerful shot with the boxer’s fists poised, ready to punch, as well as an unreleased sensitive and joyous image of him. The oversized print—each Ali is 35 inches high—pays homage to how Warhol made his wallpapers and the massive impact Ali had on the world as a humanitarian boxer.
This handscreened Air colorway has a soft, heavenly feel. It has a powdery blue background, white hands and gloves, and an ethereal silver Mylar framed in a half-toned graphite grey for the GOAT himself.
 Ali can be installed as a half drop staggered repeat, as Warhol used for his wallpapers, or it can be hung straight across if desired. The calculator results are configured for a half drop installation, so please consult your installer for quantities if you intend to install it straight across.
Andy Warhol was a leading figure in the pop art movement of the 1960s and is considered one of the most important artists of the late 20th Century. The Andy Warhol x Flavor Paper Collection represents our interpretations of Warhol's work—some iconic and others handpicked from deep in the artist's archives—released in a globally exclusive partnership with the Andy Warhol Foundation for the Visual Arts, which has been ongoing since 2013.

name: Camellias - Soft Light Eco Fibrous
description:
We collaborated with artist Evan Paul English to design a Dorothy Draper-inspired wallpaper for a champagne bar. This bold, painterly mural features massive hand-drawn flowers with a delicate feminine touch, creating the perfect backdrop on your walls or ceiling.
Soft Light has a pale grey background with pops of pink and blue in the flower petals, which allows the exquisite camellias and greenery to float gently in the foreground.
Evan Paul English is a former Flavor Paper screen printer and renowned painter, illustrator, and tattoo artist. His work draws inspiration from his collection of vintage ephemera and centers on florals, which he considers symbols of life and growth.

name: Brasilia - Silver Platinum Clay Coated Paper
description:
Brasilia is a bold, large-scale geometric pattern designed by Kravitz Design. It can be hung straight across, flipped, or in several combinations to create different looks. Lenny and his team were inspired by Brazilian art and culture, especially the architecture of its namesake city. These classic handscreened shapes create a striking look in any space.
The Silver colorway features shimmery silver ink on a platinum clay coated paper substrate, fashioning a chic monotone environment.
Kravitz Design is a conceptual creative studio founded by Lenny Kravitz in 2003. With a modern sensibility and a focus on interiors and graphic design, Kravitz Design's work always conveys a soulful elegance through a natural, relaxed sense of style.
*Please note that the calculator is set to estimate quantities based on a straight match. This will also allow randomized installation layouts.

name: Ladies - Goddess Diamond Flash
description:
Artist Katie Stout uses soft, flowing watercolor hues that gently blend into one another, creating movement and fluidity in abstract feminine forms. This confident band of babes celebrates women with beauty and lightheartedness in a visually engaging design that elevates self-expression.
A self-proclaimed "näive pop" artist, Katie Stout's maximalist work explores using craft to convey vibrantly cheerful feminity.
